.SH NAME
Net::Nostr \- Perl client and relay library for the Nostr protocol
.SH SYNOPSIS
.IX Header "SYNOPSIS"
.Vb 1
\&    use Net::Nostr;
\&
\&    # Connect to a relay as a client
\&    my $client = Net::Nostr\->client;
\&    $client\->connect("ws://relay.example.com");
\&
\&    # Run a relay
\&    my $relay = Net::Nostr\->relay;
\&    $relay\->run(\*(Aq127.0.0.1\*(Aq, 8080);
.Ve
.SH DESCRIPTION
.IX Header "DESCRIPTION"
Net::Nostr is a Perl implementation of the Nostr protocol that provides both
client and relay functionality. Most of the useful functionality lives in the
individual modules listed below \-\- start with Net::Nostr::Key for identity
management and Net::Nostr::Event for creating events.
.SH "CLASS METHODS"
.IX Header "CLASS METHODS"
.SS client
.IX Subsection "client"
.Vb 1
\&    my $client = Net::Nostr\->client;
.Ve
.PP
Convenience factory that returns a new Net::Nostr::Client instance.
Equivalent to \f(CW\*(C`Net::Nostr::Client\->new\*(C'\fR.
.SS relay
.IX Subsection "relay"
.Vb 1
\&    my $relay = Net::Nostr\->relay;
.Ve
.PP
Convenience factory that returns a new Net::Nostr::Relay instance.
Equivalent to \f(CW\*(C`Net::Nostr::Relay\->new\*(C'\fR.
